-- Global Funds Buy Net 11.8 Billion Rupees of Indian Derivatives
-- B y   P a r e s h   J a t a k i a
-- 2012-01-30T03:30:22Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-30/global-funds-buy-net-11-8-billion-rupees-of-indian-derivatives.html
Global investors  bought a  net 11.8
billion rupees ($239 million) of Indian equity  derivatives  on
Jan. 27, according to the National Stock Exchange of India Ltd.  Open interest, or the number of contracts outstanding in
value terms, rose 5.9 percent to 679.2 billion rupees, or 34.2
percent of the gross market position, according to the
exchangeâ€™s website. Open interest reached a record 1.6 trillion
rupees on Sept. 21, 2010.  Foreign funds bought a net 12.4 billion rupees of shares in
the  cash  segment on Jan. 27, according to preliminary data given
by the bourse.  To contact the reporter on this story:
